        <h3 class="display-4">One-Hour Pizza Dough</h3>
    </div>
    
    <div class="content">
        <p>
            While I love the art of Neapolitan Pizza, I don't always have the time to make the dough and let it ferment for 24 hours.  For those times, I have found a great recipe for a one-hour pizza.  
            This recipe became a favorite of my wife and I soon after our marriage.  We decided to have pizza for dinner, but being poor college students, we didn't have the money to order out.  We scoured 
            the internet and stumbled upon a recipe for a one-hour pizza dough.  We were skeptical, but we decided to give it a try.  The recipe was simple, and the dough was easy to make.  We were amazed at 
            the flavor and great texture of the dough.  We have been using this recipe ever since.  The recipe can be found <a href="https://www.thursdaynightpizza.com/1-hour-pizza-dough/" target="_blank">here</a>.  
            A few notes for this pizza, we usually cook this dough in our 11-inch cast iron skillet.  We preheat the skillet on the stove, then coat it with olive oil, then we stretch the dough to fit the skillet.  
            This makes for a great deep dish style pizza that has remained one of our family favorites.
        </p>
    </div>
    
